# TTS Configuration Example
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values

# ============================================================================
# OpenAI TTS (Optional - required only for OpenAI provider as fallback)
# ============================================================================
# Get your API key from: https://platform.openai.com/account/api-keys
# Only needed if using OpenAI as primary or fallback provider
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-api-key-here

# ============================================================================
# Piper TTS Configuration (Local, recommended)
# ============================================================================
# Piper is a fast, offline neural TTS engine. No configuration needed
# after installation. Set voice using --voice flag or DEFAULT_VOICES in
# scripts/generate-audio.js
#
# Install Piper:
#   pip install piper-tts
#
# Download voice models:
#   piper --download en_US-lessac-medium
#
# List available voices:
#   piper --list-voices
#

# ============================================================================
# Coqui TTS Configuration (Local)
# ============================================================================
# Coqui is a flexible neural TTS with multiple model options
#
# Install Coqui:
#   pip install TTS
#
# The library will auto-download models on first use
#
# Available models:
#   - glow-tts (fast, good quality)
#   - tacotron2 (high quality)
#   - align-tts (adaptive)
#

# ============================================================================
# Recommended Setup
# ============================================================================
# 1. Install Piper first (fast, offline, good quality)
#    pip install piper-tts
#    piper --download en_US-lessac-medium
#
# 2. Use it by default:
#    npm run generate-audio
#
# 3. Have Coqui as secondary fallback:
#    pip install TTS
#
# 4. Have OpenAI as premium fallback (optional):
#    Set OPENAI_API_KEY above
#    npm run generate-audio:openai
#
# The script auto-detects available providers and uses them in this order:
# 1. Piper (local, fast, offline)
# 2. Coqui (local, flexible)
# 3. OpenAI (cloud, premium quality)
